Crackland is a 24 hour drugs market in the slums of Rio de Janeiro . 
  Crack cocaine users visit the open-air bazaars to buy rocks of the drug and smoke it in plain sight . 
  Brazil has become the world's top consumer of crack cocaine . 
  The market is home to people from all walks of life including pregnant mothers and homeless addicts . 
  The photographer used the market as a backdrop for a portrait project . 
 